00:28:12.240 --> 00:28:16.680
The second I would say is,

00:28:16.760 --> 00:28:19.680
you know, we've run out of public data.

00:28:20.520 --> 00:28:23.200
And we talked about RL
in a different context earlier,

00:28:23.280 --> 00:28:27.320
but reinforcement learning
has been the primary technique

00:28:27.400 --> 00:28:30.560
for with which models
get better over time.

00:28:30.640 --> 00:28:34.000
And acquiring data to do
good reinforcement learning is

00:28:34.080 --> 00:28:36.360
quite different than how you would
acquire data otherwise.

00:28:36.440 --> 00:28:37.920
So that is another trend.

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:39.560
So when everybody
runs out of data,

00:28:39.640 --> 00:28:41.920
they create synthetic
and keep improving the model?

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:43.360
It's not exactly like that.

00:28:43.440 --> 00:28:45.440
I mean,
in reinforcement learning, you basically

00:28:45.520 --> 00:28:48.880
want an environment where
there is certain rewards you can get,

00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:50.920
sometimes they're extremely
verifiable rewards,

00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:52.840
in which case it be RLVR,

00:28:52.920 --> 00:28:55.240
sometimes they're more nuanced,
where it's like text.

00:28:55.320 --> 00:28:56.520
Like how do you verify that?

00:28:56.600 --> 00:28:59.800
But there are... you can use an LLM
as a judge to verify that.

00:28:59.880 --> 00:29:02.120
So there's various kinds of rewards,
but it's...

00:29:02.200 --> 00:29:03.680
One way to think about it is, yes,

00:29:03.760 --> 00:29:06.520
you are generating an environment
where there's rewards

00:29:06.600 --> 00:29:10.600
and you're making the model
become better at that task.

00:29:10.680 --> 00:29:15.240
In a similar way that you would do,
for example, when Google did AlphaGo

00:29:15.320 --> 00:29:17.520
and you train an AI to learn a game,

00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:19.640
you have a reward,
which is winning the game

00:29:19.720 --> 00:29:21.600
and then you figure out the steps
in the middle.

00:29:22.400 --> 00:29:25.080
So it's not really synthetic data per se.

00:29:25.160 --> 00:29:27.960
That is also used,
but it's a different step.

00:29:28.040 --> 00:29:30.760
But that's what I meant
by reinforcement learning.

00:29:30.840 --> 00:29:32.720
