00:34:02.520 --> 00:34:05.480
where we will claim AGI is not here
maybe ten years from now,

00:34:05.560 --> 00:34:07.360
but it's already kind of here.

00:34:07.440 --> 00:34:09.600
In the not theoretical
definition maybe,

00:34:09.680 --> 00:34:12.840
but in a capabilities perspective,
it's already better.

00:34:12.920 --> 00:34:16.280
Yeah, and I think another area
that's becoming critically important

00:34:16.360 --> 00:34:19.520
is like, what is the data set
and the models

00:34:19.600 --> 00:34:23.360
that we can use to recreate
the physical world.

00:34:23.440 --> 00:34:27.400
So, in the world where we can have
a lot of the robots that would do

00:34:27.480 --> 00:34:30.880
a bunch of the manual labour
that it's hard to hire people for

00:34:30.960 --> 00:34:33.360
because they don't want to
or it's expensive,

00:34:34.680 --> 00:34:37.240
how do you get to the five nines
that you've described?

00:34:38.080 --> 00:34:41.040
And you know, there are not that many
companies use the example

00:34:41.120 --> 00:34:45.000
of autonomous vehicles
that have been taking photos,

00:34:45.080 --> 00:34:48.320
videos and other inputs
of the offline world,

00:34:48.400 --> 00:34:51.640
like Waymo, Tesla,
there are a few companies.

00:34:51.720 --> 00:34:55.800
So where else, you know, can you find
other sources of such data?

00:34:55.880 --> 00:34:58.480
Either real world data
or synthetic data

00:34:58.560 --> 00:35:03.360
on the cheap, that's labelled
and easily ready to use.

00:35:04.280 --> 00:35:10.000
This is a very important space and has
applications that can be in defence-tech,

00:35:10.080 --> 00:35:12.600
and all sorts of robotics.

00:35:12.680 --> 00:35:14.280
Yeah, so many, many.

00:35:14.360 --> 00:35:19.120
This embodied intelligence space,
how you feed them with data,

00:35:19.200 --> 00:35:25.240
it's going to be one of the most amazing
ones to do business in the next few years.

00:35:25.320 --> 00:35:27.640
Do you think there's a use case
in India for that?

00:35:28.520 --> 00:35:30.400
For specifically what Niko said?

00:35:30.480 --> 00:35:34.400
-Yeah.
-Oh, that's a complicated one.

