"It's just the internet,
yada, yada, yada, yada."

00:37:55.560 --> 00:37:59.400
If you look up this paper
called Alpha Evolve from DeepMind,

00:37:59.480 --> 00:38:02.520
it is literally a paper where
there are these simple math problems

00:38:02.600 --> 00:38:05.880
that everybody can understand,
which is, you know, hexagon packing.

00:38:05.960 --> 00:38:11.640
You have a hexagon, how many
of 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, up to n hexagons

00:38:11.720 --> 00:38:14.080
can you fit and how big
is the surrounding hexagon?

00:38:14.160 --> 00:38:17.280
How small can you get the hexagon
and pack all of this stuff in?

00:38:17.360 --> 00:38:22.840
And Alpha Evolve has made novel solutions
on this problem that, you know,

00:38:22.920 --> 00:38:25.560
that haven't been improved
upon in 20, 30 years.

00:38:25.640 --> 00:38:31.840
So just to be clear, like AI is very much
pushing the frontiers of human knowledge,

00:38:31.920 --> 00:38:34.600
just in bits and pieces today
and we're going to see more of it.

00:38:34.680 --> 00:38:37.080
But I just wanted to throw
that one out there.

